  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You create a curtain of powerfully gusting winds, which reaches up to 1 ft per level high and is 2 ft thick. The roaring gale tears paper and similar light materials out of people's hands (Reflex negates). Any Small or smaller creatures cannot pass through the barrier. Loose items may be sent flying upward when caught in the wall, and arrows and bolts passing through are deflected upwards, missing entirely. Other ranged weapons passing through the wall have a 30% miss chance, though exceptionally large or heavy weapons (such as siege weapons) are immune, as are ballistic weapons. Gases and gas-based attacks cannot pass through the wall, nor can any creature in a gas-like form.<br><br>The wall is vertical, but can be shaped in any continuous path along the ground. It cannot be made to completely enclose a location on its own.</p>\n\n\n\n",
